\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid16262158 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You were born in 1886?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was it here in Lerwick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, in Edinburgh. Come here as a boy. Six year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Why did you move here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well my parents belonged here and my father was a seaman. And there was a pediment of smallpox in Leith and Edinburgh and there was a case, we lived in a flatted house and my mother -
 there was a case just next door and she took three boys and proceeded - home, shall I say, and we're here yet. We never went away again. We just stopped here and my father was a seaman you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was he a seaman all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - the bulk of i
t. When he came ashore when he got kind of elderly he went doing another job. But - we've been - my two brothers and - they're both gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You had two brothers, did you have any sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, I'd no sisters, just the two brothers. One was two year
s younger and the other four years younger. Yes. My mother lived until she was a hundred and two years and six month. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When did she die then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She died in 1950. She was born in 1848 in Collafirth Delfing. Collafirth. Delting. And she lived wi
th - died here in this house when she was a hundred and two years and six month exactly and - she was pretty good even that time, she - fell like but didn't break anything but I think the shock just finished it. Yes. And my father had died oh many years b
efore that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How old was he then when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh he was only seventy. Aye, he was only seventy. He went for an operation - prostrate and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When would that be that he died?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh '28.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your mother ever have any jobs or did she not work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh no, no, she never - no, no, she just looked after us. Plenty to do doing that. Three boys. Oh no, no she never did any work after she married, not her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So you lived in Lerwick after you were six, what sort of a house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It was a tenement house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Can you tell me what those were like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well that was a - house probably with four tenants in it, quite a good house we had. Kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Near the Harbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, it was down in Market Street, we - there were no houses much about the harbour then, no, and we lived there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How many rooms are there in a tenement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well there was three rooms that we had in the tenement and - by that time we had the gas and - and sanitary. It was a very good one of their kind. Yes. There were four tenants in it and - two down and two up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Who was it owned by, was it a council one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh no, there were no council house then. Oh no, no, there were no council houses then. Just a landlord, private landlord and it was quite a good strong house. Very good. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It's not still standing is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes, it's still standing now. Down in Market Street. Still there. Aye. Yes. It's just on the left hand side and the last one down before you come to that - what's the name of the place that's the - is the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14179521\charrsid8147471 cook shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 there? Yes. Right there, yes. That's a private house now you know, somebody bought it. But - old house you know. That was - that's a long time ago. Bu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14179521\charrsid8147471 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14179521\charrsid8147471 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  quite a good house yet. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And your mother looked after you without anybody to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes, and my father was seldom home. Oh no, maybe come home once a year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 He'd be away all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, he was always all that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She did the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - oh yes, the old wash tube and all scrubber that you scrubbed on, there was no - no - nothing like it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 then days}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
. Lots of these houses would do their scrubbing outside. Oh - had the - big wooden tubs and the washing board and - and do their scrubbing to keep the house clean out
side. Yes, carry out the water. We - in that house we had the water in the house and had a sink and a toilet and - yes, but there wasn't many houses in Lerwick had had that. Very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So you were very fortunate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Very fortunate, yes, yes, I think
 there were many - weren't very many houses in the - in the lines of Lerwick at that time that had anything but a - an outside - hardly had an outside - had to go to a public - yes, and - they'd no water laid in, just pump outside that they went and fetch
ed in. Fetched the water as they required it. And all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
he lanes. That was - and that was right up maybe to about 1900 and coming on. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your mother have a sort of regular daily routine of housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh very. Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you tell me how that went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well she was up every morning about seven and we went to school, Charlie and I was the oldest and well you went out and delivered milk or - things like that and come back and got your porridge and went to school. She was a very methodical
 old woman as well then. Because she had the three young boys to look after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have to help her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Not very much. Not very much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there anything that you had to do in the house regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. No, I can't remember anything of that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have to look after your younger brothers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes, help them and - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Take them out sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Look after them as they were playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. I was - well my mother - I was the oldest and sort of - looked on me as the - boss of the show and - you see, the boys, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Who would light the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh my mother did. Oh my mother - oh yes, my mother did that, oh yes, she did it all, looked after the coal f
ire. We'd a coal fire and - we'd no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 gas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
. We just had paraffin lamps. Well the majority of people in Lerwick at that time had paraffin lamps. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 See, that was the days before even the mantles, the gas mantles came. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It was only a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 burner}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , flame burner. And -
 and all that but we had no gas in the house, we just had paraffin lamps. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did she make clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, she didna make any clothes but she - she repaired them. Yes, repaired them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She wouldn't make shoes?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. But - she had a brother that - who was in the shoe business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And he made the shoes for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, he made them and looking after them. Yes. And - and in the course of time he came and stopped with us. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 He was there living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. He came - home from Edinburgh as well and - and opened a business here and he lived with - at that time he wasn't married. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So he was really rather like your father in a way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes, he was like that, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did he help about the house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, no, my mother did all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Who would do the decorating?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh we had to get in a man to do. Same as we do yet. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you expected to go to bed at a regular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Nine o'clock. Nine o'clock. Every night. Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, well when we got on a bit we put ourselves to bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You ate in the kitchen did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we ate in the kitchen. Oh the kitchen was a room the side of this and we ate there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You said you started breakfast with porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes, porridge every morning and still the same. Still the same, yes. The doctor asks Bertha my daughter, does he take it on Sundays? Yes, she says, he takes it on Sundays as well. And I still take it. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 I always call it the poultice, hot milk poultice - inside. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have anything else at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, no. Oh no. And I've nothing ever yet. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What would you usually eat for midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh we'd generally have a dinner of something and soup, my mother was a great believer -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She made soups did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh yes, she made a lot of soup and - she baked all her own bread, oh yes, all bread and made her own jam. Yes. Rhubarb jam entirely 'cos we got it for nothing. Yes Yes, and she made the jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you eat fish for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh yes, we had fish occasionally and we generally had some form of meat at dinner time, yes. Soup. Yes. Some form - maybe rice or - or - other things, cornflower or something else for your dinner. See milk wasna v
ery dear then, we could get plenty of milk. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So the main meal of the day was midday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Oh yes, when you come home from school at dinner time you had your dinner, you had the main meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And then in the evening you had another meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 We had - generally had what we called our tea. Six o'clock or that, might have got an egg or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But not so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, not - well, egg and plenty of bread and - we called it bannocks and butter. Yes. Yes. They're all home made and that. And Be
rtha still makes them yet. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever have any tinned food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. Wasn't heard of then. The only thing that ever - remembered being tinned then was corned beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You did have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 That was - yes, why I remember - remember always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 a pound tin or corned beef. It wasna very dear, maybe sixpence or sevenpence I think, yes. Yes. That was the only corned - tinned food that we ever had you see, nothing in package - no package foods then. You see. If you went in and bought tea well 
- the man in the shop he filled up a paper bag and weighted it. Yes. And like sugar the - like nowadays it's all packaged but - he filled up the bag - paper bag - and - everything flour, meal. Yes, syrup, well they had it and you went there with a jelly -
 jelly jug and bought it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You took your own jug of this then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes. Well just ordinary jam jug and he held it in and - and - filled them up with syrup or treacle and - yes, dinna cost very much but - no, and molasses. Yes, that was the three that 
you could get that you could buy and he just turned on the tap and run it in. Oh aye, a - that - my uncle's a great man on the cold oil and he used to get the fish - fish livers and make this cod liver oil and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 For a medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 We had it every d
ay. We got it every time - you buy cod liver now. But he - he; made sure that we always had our spoon of cod liver oil and it wasna just very good to take I can assure you. No, no, but we had to get it. And maybe was - maybe the result of it, me living so
 long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did he or your mother make any medicines though?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. Oh no, no, no. We never had any medicines. No, we never had medicine, no. I never remember any medicines. No, no, no, no. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They couldn't keep any hens or animals of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, not in - not - not there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You didn't have an allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. No, no. Just the piece, like the back, drying the clothes. No, no, we'd no - nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When you were having meals were you allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I - don't think there was ever any - thing about that. Well there was never any restrictions that ever I knew about. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 Boys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  talked away and they were too busy maybe - satisfying their hunger that they didna bother to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your mother mind if you didn't finish your food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - I don't think she were ever - had that to do. We were always ready for it. That age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you allowed to pick and choose at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, no. No, no. Never, no, no, she did all that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was she very strict about how you sat had held your knife and fork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, very particular about that, yes, very particular. Very - as we would say, kind of tiddly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 bring}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  a book to the table if you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well, not at that time but latterly - you'd maybe sit and read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When you'd finished did she mind when you left the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, you just left - we all sat, we never left one by one, we just all - we had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You wait 'til the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 We had to wait - oh we always had to wait 'til the end, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have grace at meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes, oh yes. Always, always. She was a very religious woman, my mother, yes, and we - far back as I can remember - we always had then what we called our Sunday clothes and we always got - and we
nt to church every Sunday morning, as far back as I can remember. And - we were brought up in the church practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The parish church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Parish church of Scotland. Bible every night. We had to sit and read. Verses out of the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes. And she said the prayers every night, she - first I would, oldest, and then the second and that was - we were getting up then, you know, could read. Maybe ten, twelve and fourteen, see. Yes. And we'd do that and then she'll have us to s
ing hymns. Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. But she was a very strong church woman you know and we - oh well, it was just something you were born and brought up in you know, so it continues with you, my brothers and I were - three of us were all elders of the Church 
of Scotland here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Your mother was an elder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
No, my - my two brothers and myself when they were men, yes, and I am still the senior member elder of the church and my other two brothers and it was rather unique, it had never been known before, thre
e brothers were elders of the same church. And indeed I - I'm still there. I was at church on Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, Sunday school was always at three o'clock in the afternoon. Yes. Well it was just the two events and wh
en we were boys and that was what we used to say was the Sunday school picnic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh you just went to a field and played games. When it was won and then had these refreshments outside and there were races and tug o'war and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Where did they do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They - they went to the park out here at Sound you see, they had to walk it then. Oh you had to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 There were no carts?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh there were no cars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They didn't take you in a wagonette?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh n
o, no, no, no, not - see you'd maybe three hundred children there at Sunday school in them days. Oh my, my yes. I've seen that same church you know Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 Lambie's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  church. Well I've seen them carrying maybe on a communion Sunday I've seen them carrying in seats and chairs - seven or eight hundred people in there. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did they do in the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well, they just - give you sort of scripture questions and you had to learn them and answer them all on the following Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, there was no temperance class but - in Lerwick we had - we had the Dependant Order of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 Raccabites}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  which you maybe don't know. Well that is a temperance society. And - they had the hall up there called the Planets in Mount Hoole
y Street and that was the building they had and - and that - and I am still the last surviving member here of the Independent Order and they had the juniors and then they had the seniors. Then we had another temperance order here called the Good Templars 
and they were the juniors and the seniors. And then the Wesleyan church had what was called the Band of Hope which was to t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 each}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 you the temperance there. And I was temperate then and I'm still. I never was in a public house in my life and I never drank a glass of whisky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was your mother temperate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Very. Very strong. And my two brothers were the same. There were never any drink among the three of us and we grew, they died, temperate and I'm the same yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And you joined as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we 
joined - you see there were more chances of boys to be taught of temperance then. See you went there to a weekly meeting and - and you had a romp through the hall and they'd give you a bit of a lecture and you maybe sung some temperance hymns. But that's 
all. None of that now. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you think drink was a bad problem in the town at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well my mother did think it, I mean, she was very strong in teaching us these - about temperance. And - well I wouldn't say - I would say it's worse now. Oh - oh - worse now, yes. Well you see girls and women and all going into pubs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The girls never went in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh never - I never knew anything - never seen 'em going in, I never heard of 'em being in then. No. Never heard of it when I was a boy an
d it's only I would say since this last war that this has come up. Of course there was no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 here for - pubs that year. No, no, it - we had this local veto pause in Lerwick for Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When was the local veto then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - I think it was changed here after the war about - 1950 would it have been, I couldn't just - I know there'd been }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 local}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  veto for thirty-two years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But when you were a boy there wasn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, oh no, oh no, there were plenty of pubs then but there was no - y
ou never heard of women or girls going in pubs then, not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It was mostly sailors was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes, well maybe the local men took a dram at one time for - for that on an evening or that but - I would say it's - bad here now, the same it
's getting bad all over Scotland. Never heard of girls and that going into pubs, women, I never heard of it in the old times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you allowed to play any games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. No, no. Oh no, no, not - no, none whatever. We went for a walk and
 that yes, but never no game on the Sunday. Oh no. None at all. That was just the custom here, I wouldn't - you never seen any boys or out - or girls out playing here on a - a Sunday way back seventy year ago. Oh no. Very quiet day, yes. And Sunday school
 was always held at three o'clock on Sunday afternoon. Was always very reverent and very quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was you say your mother was an easy person to talk to, if you had any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 
worries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  could you talk to her about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes. Oh yes. Discussed it with my mother, yes. Yes. And she discussed it with me being the oldest. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 If another child }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 hurt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  you would she say you should hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well I - can't mind much but - she - I mind her - my other brother that was next brother he was quarrelling wi
th a boy which she thought she had seen the whole thing and she thought }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 Will}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 had deserved what he was getting and behaved himself the other boy wouldna have been punching him. She was very even and - on that. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 If you did something that she disapproved of would she punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
No, she didna - never did much of that. No, no. I never saw my mother striking us at all. But she would lecture for anything, lecture you, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Use reason always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She would be much more of an influence on you that your father because he wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes, we never saw much of him. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would it be a special day when he came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh very special when he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What would you do to celebrate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh, we used 
to go down and meet him at the boat and - and see what he had and if he'd brought you anything I suppose, the same as they do now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What sort of boats was he going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh well, the first of his days he was in the bark or he maybe went in the
 sailing ships away to Australia and that. Oh yes, in the first of his time, he went to Australia and sailed in - these big sailing ships and latterly then, after he'd married and settled down he - went on - coasters as we call them, maybe away for a week
 or three weeks. Up - up the Baltic or round Spain or that. Yes, but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was he ever a captain of a ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, no, he never was nothing but just a seaman. Seaman. All his time at sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were there any other special days, what about a birthday, was a birthday a special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well, we would - we just always had our little bit of a tea among ourselves and - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Oh you would get something from your mother and that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh we always just had something the same like what they have you know the Christmas there and you'd probably get something for your mother and - yes. My father, if it was possible he'd maybe try and be home at Christmas, he liked to come home. Y
es. Sometimes it didn't always work out. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there anyone in the family who played music or sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
We were all very musical. Yes. And - my daughter plays in the orchestra - one. And I played the violin. And my youngest brother played the viol
in and my - the one between us played the piano. I wouldn't say he was very perfect in it but he did play the piano, we had a piano. Yes, but - my uncle played the violin but not my mother. But - my brother and me played the violin. Very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you play together at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes. Yes, play together at home and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well - I don't think we ever did much singing and maybe just usually when you went to the church and that, you didna sing much in the house at that time. But we went to a teacher that taught the violin and learned the music. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you play the Shetland music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - oh yes, I could play the reels, what we call the reels and - and that and the jigs, Irish jigs and that, oh we could play all
 he Shetland. We called them Shetland }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698518\charrsid8147471 reels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 but I don't suppose it ever - it always ourselves called Shetland reels. Yes, but it was just Scot or music somewhere. But - I know we could both read the music. And I can still - I can't play now but I can read the music and that. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - no, there werena much books but - that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Reccabites}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  as I told you I went to join it as a boy and my brothers and all joined it, they had a library and I remembered I think I read
 all the most of Dickens and the most of Scott. Yes. And other books as well. All very much on the reading. Yes. My mother - was inveterate reader. Yes, 'cos I remember every night when we was tucked in at night and she went away in the kitchen and got on
 and would sit and read 'til midnight I used to think she never slept any. Yes. But, you know, she used to - buy the wool and she had a spinning wheel and - yes, and card it, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 teased}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  up the wool you know, you can }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 tease}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 it all and pour oil on it and - and carded it you know. Sat and carded and trim it all and card it and then spun it and twined it, made the yarn of the wool then sat and knit. It was mostly shawls they knitted then, there was no - not much }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 jumpers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , mostly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 shawls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , underwear and that. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She did that to sell it then, was this to earn more money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, oh yes, oh they sold the shawls, they made the shawls and - and sold them - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Who would she sell them to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well there was hardly any buyers in Lerwick - oh there were may
be a dozen buyers in Lerwick that dealt in this - the Shetland hosiery. Yes, I'm telling them about my mother doing the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Those are the three brothers are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, that's them. Yes. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Are those your Sunday suits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, that's right, that the Sunday clothes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there somebody who came round to her and arranged for this work, a factor or an agent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 For the wool? Oh no, no, you just asked - after you'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 made}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  the shawls then you went down and tried selli
ng them - different shops. You went to the one that would give you the most for it. And that was - that was a great way that they did it, very few of them give you like cash. Like the drapers shop would give you draperies and maybe kept - another shop may
be kept groceries and he would give you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 groceries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
. But if he give you cash he took a threepence off the shilling, you see. He probably give you - if he give you five shillings say for the article well, you wanted cash he took a threepence off and you got fo
ur shillings. And if you took goods then you got five shillings. Yes, but he wasn't allowed to do that, that was the truck system you see. But - oh - it was all - it was all done you know. Oh it was all - very few ever give you cash. Yes. Like down there 
at Anderson and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Courtney\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 - hosiery shop, it was mostly all tea, was a big drapers shop and you could go by the door of that shop and smell the tea and could always get a pound a tea or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 a half}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your mother read aloud?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, no, she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 read}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  only to herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did she read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh when she read to us she read aloud, oh yes. Oh yes, we'd sit around and he'd read to us, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Mostly from the Bible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Yes, oh yes. And we read}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  a verse about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would she read other books to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - oh she was a - no, no. I wouldn't - no, no, we - she le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 t that us to do ourselves, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you go out visiting friends in the evenings as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well occasionally, but not much. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would people come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, people would come in. I remember - my ministers here and that's what, Crawford's time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Anyway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 say 1900 when he was here I think was may have been five. 1900. And he used to go among like tenement houses and have what was called a - can't remember w
ords but was - they had meetings in the house. Yes, and he used to read - maybe read a chapter from the Bible and sing hymns. Cottage meetings they called it, Cottage Meetings, yes. But he was the last one that did it. And I would say that he went - went 
away about - 1900. But normally service in a church doesn't arise now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 In the country I'm told that the neighbours used to come in and out all the time without knocking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh -- oh yes, oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was that the same in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, not so 
much in the town. No, no. In the country they never shut any doors at night, they never shut any doors, 'cos there was nobody there, just a croft up the road and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But it was different in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, oh you shut your door in the town. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And you didn't come in unless you were invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
No. No, not as - you wouldn't come except you were - you knocked at the door and that. But that's very much the custom in some of the country places yet I think. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 If your mother was ill or something like that would the neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, oh yes, oh they were very good like that. Oh yes, come and help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Occasionally. We went sometimes to the country. To friends of ours up in De
lting but we never went off the island. No, no, 'til we were grown up. I think I'd been fourteen. I once went off the island at that time, we went back to Edinburgh for a holiday and we went from here to Leith in the boat - called at Aberdeen and - then t
o
 Leith and - fifteen shillings return for as - and adult and half price for children. Second class. Fifteen shillings return from here to Leith. Now you can't get a bed under - for fifteen shillings. And you took your own food with you, took sandwiches or
 something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What happened on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I - I don't think we noticed much of them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Oh no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , they never took any notice of that. No. No, no, we just had generally had - Christmas and New Year and - and Queen's birthday, Victoria - Queen Victo
ria's birthday was in the month of May, that called the May holiday. That was all the holidays that was here. Yes. And the shops - shops all opened at eight o'clock in the morning and shut at nine. Oh yes, long day and - and working people like labourers 
or even tradesmen, joiners in them days started at six and finished at six. Yes, in the morning. Long days then. But - they survived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What about your school, when did you go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh we went at five. When we were five year old. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did you think of the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh it was all right, I remember going to school and liked it very much. Yes, oh yes. You went and you got your own book for tuppence. Oh all - you bought all your own schoolbooks. Right up 'til the time that I was left the school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Which school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - over here what's - what do you call this one there, no, the big school, the other one along side. Infant? No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Yes there - over here - the school just over here and then we went from there up to what's called Anderson Institute then - up there, there was the secondary school and - Central school.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you like the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh well I suppose that - some of them you liked and some you disliked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I've heard they used these -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 O
h very much when I was at school and even when Bertha was. They're not so bad with Vera I think. I mind Bertha saying how the teachers when she went around to correct the jotters she always took the strap with her. And used them as she went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did the teachers emphasise anything special like punctuality or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They did then. They were more interested in the pupils I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You think they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I think so. I think so. Yes, there were just the personal touch with the children then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you remember any general elections when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. I mind one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your father take any interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 My father? No, my father was never here then when elections were on, but I as a boy I might be very young going
 to the meetings in the Town Hall and - packed out the Town Hall then. Great interest. I mind and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4485709\charrsid8147471 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
hen the - Lyle he must have been here a Liberal for many many years. Then a man come up here and he stood as a Conservative. His name was Wason. Wason, that 
was the man that sat in the House of Commons and knitted socks. Yes. And he and another boy they were both about six feet four and he always, when he was going to speak and look at you used to wear these glasses, he looked like this. I think I see him loo
k
ing yet. Mind I mind asking him when he went back to the Commons would he move the Dutch off the Minister of Education salary by a hundred pound. I - I think I see him yet putting on this one eyed spec, he says, most emphatically no. He had a brother, the
y were both solicitors but they must have had plenty of money. And they were both over six feet. One was - Huston and the other one was - can't mind his name. Eugene Wason and - oh I don't mind the other one's name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you take sides as boys in the election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh no. Oh, we had the bonfires. We always had a bonfire when - M.P. got in. Oh yes, a bonfire on the hill. Celebrate, yes, and yet we didn't know hardly what they was doing it for. The bonfire was maybe more interesting as the test of it. Yes
. And at that time he used to - wait and - when he was standing there we had the two local papers, the Shetland Times and the Shetland News then. One represented the - the Tory and the other the Liberal. And they used to post the whole this - all the spee
c
hes was in the local paper on either side, and everybody in Lerwick got a copy and posted to them through Shetland. Copy of the Shetland News and the Shetland Times, with each of them speeches. And - and then they hired the Earl of Zetland to go up to Yel
l and that you see, there wasn't much chance of get their own Shetlander, except by sea. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 There was less to do in the town I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh, plenty of people now outside the town hardly 'cos there was nothing to go with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there's theatre in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, but there were - we all liked the Gilbert and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Sullivan\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  and all that was all being produced in Lerwick when I was a boy. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You went to concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, oh yes. And you used to get concert parties come up here from A
berdeen. Man called Culbert used to come, you know, and there was another man called Kilbertle, he used to come and give a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 couple}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  of nights up in the Town Hall and shilling and sixpence to the bairns and the boys. Yes. And we used to - well that was much later - there used to be a circus that come up here. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4485709\charrsid8147471 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
. Above here where the playing fields is, you mind the circus Bertha? And - well where the playing fields is of a Saturday. But they never had any elephants or anything like that. Couple of horses, they had a couple of horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have pocket money as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no very much of that. Maybe a couple of coppers. Maybe pennies. And very early in life you got your Saturday penny. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you earn that though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, no, you just - 
that was an understanding and you spent a half one at one time. Looking in the window for something for a ha'penny and then bought it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did you get for a penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh just candy of some kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You said you started work when you were at school as a milk boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Delivering milk in the morning, seven o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did you do after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh well, I was in butcher trade first and then me mother insisted I go and serve my time with my uncle in the shoe trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You had to do seven years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, no. No, no, it was just five. Five years. Only trade as ever I knew of having to serve seven years was apprentice. Yes, apprentice.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you think it made a great difference in those days if you'd served your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - it was generally known that - it was much better for every boy to learn a trade. You see, instead to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 grow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  up and to be a - a labourer or that and - most of all boys went and learned a trade, served his time like, at all trades, tailors and shoema
kers and joiners and - and everything. Oh - you see - it - there were very much - very little ready made clothing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 And there were no much ready made shoes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It was all done by hand. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You learnt to make the whole of the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes. But you 
see, there were no rubber then. No, all - everything was leather. There was no rubber thenadays. All what you see the fishermen wearing up here now, rubber boots, were all made of leather. It's always on order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 That gave you quite a lot of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, oh a lot of work. Was all done by hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How many were there in the family that did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , how many working in the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Well - my uncle's shop, the last shop that I was ink that - and I was in it all me life, there was nineteen started. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
But there's none now. There's no tradesmen now in Lerwick. Like tailors, there's no such a thing as a tailors. You see, everybody then had to go to tailors get your clothes made except for you bought a ready made and it wasn't much good. Yes. Your moth
er, she always got the scraps and - for the patching and - you got the seat of your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 trousers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 out or got ripped on a nail or something. My goodness me, it's changed. There's no shoemakers and no tailors in Shetland, in Lerwick or in Shetland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How long were you a shoemaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I was - well for a part of my life and then I was in the business there and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You went into another business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, the same business. I was there for fifty year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It was your own business in the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It was your uncle's at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, my uncle. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your brothers go into the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh well they were - they were - one was a cook, another was a baker. Yes. Yes, but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  didna finish there. Oh no. Changed over to other - jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How many people were working in your uncle's business in about 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh he'd had about - half a dozen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And then it was later that there was nineteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes. Yes, nineteen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 You made}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
No, no. No, no, I'm saying I - I remember the first one that came to Shetland, the three wheeled bicycle. And - when it came here and - somebody said, oh see what's going past, and people went out and had a look at it. Previous to that you know, the pedal
s on it, when you went down a hill you got your feet like this, there was spikes and you - the pedals kept flying around all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It must have been rather frightening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you cycle far?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 All round the island - how far did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh well, I was been quite a good bit 'cos my pal and me, each had one to start with and we used to go cycling way down to Dunrossness and that way. I - I've seen a fair amount of the mainland you know, for about twenty mile around.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It must have made a great difference to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh it did. There were plenty of people in Lerwick in 1900 had never been out of Lerwick. Maybe walked to Scalloway or across the Bressay with the ferry which you paid a - penny was a - but
 a sail boat. There were no motors or any kind. No cars. I mind the first cars that came to Shetland. Yes. And I remember - Cairnson Brothers - he was a big - contractor with the car - with the horses and carts and gigs and all that and they took this car
 up to show 'em and he looked the car and - oh we would maybe kept maybe about thirty }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 horses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 that time. And he says, you might treat the horses reckless but you'll not treat that. That's meaning the car. She wouldna go very fast then nothing above - very go
od. The car would have to get filled up with petrol what he was meaning, he called it the cars breakfast. You can cheat the horse out of his breakfast wouldna cheat the car of his breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When you went out bicycling did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no,
 no. No. But later I did go a little - I never was greatly interested in the - but this pal of mine was. Greatly interested in the trout fishing and I would go with him but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have any hobbies as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well the most hobby that I had was the playing of the violin. Yes. I played a lot with the violin, yes. Of course we played football.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you in a team?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 We - Oh yes, I - I have photographs way up in the top of the house and that. Yes. Played football. I was in the old volunteers
. Yes. Before it changed over to the Territorials, and I was at the review in Edinburgh in 1905. And then I was at opening of Maris}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 els}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 College in Aberdeen, along with the Volunteers doing duty in the streets you know. And kind Edward opened - Marischels 
College in Aberdeen. And I was away with that as well. Maybe about eighty of the Volunteers. Before the Territorials came into force it was called the Volunteers. This was the seventh Volunteer }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  the Gordon Highlanders. B.B.G.H.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How many days a year did you have to spend in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well - here we never went to camp. In the mainland they all went to camp but here was these busy time of year and the fishing and you couldna get and you put on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 extra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  drills, you see, we used to have to do sixteen drills in a year. But if you went to camp you didn't do that, so we did here we did the drills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 That's days its it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, you sometime - at night, you went - when you went to camp you went for a couple of weeks but here we did the drills on dif
ferent days. Different things you did, if you went for a church parade you - got two and you went for - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 night out you would get four. Four drills and so on. They were easy put in you see. Yes, and then of course it changed into the Territorials. And - and I left after they got - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 kilt}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 . I thought I - wouldna put in with the kilt and I left. I think I put in about seven years maybe. I joined when I was seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Can you tell me again about how you carried the pails?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh there were two 
to carry it, it was a big pail you know. And we had a lid on it and we had measure which hooked on the lid into the milk and then we took the measure out, held a pint or half a pint and poured it into the peoples' - whatever they brought to get it in, the
 vessel that they brought in, a jog or a bowl. Went from house to house delivering the milk. Some paid you and others paid it weekly and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It was quite heavy to carry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - and who came with me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  the daughter of man that owned it all. And her
 and I went around with milk every morning, seven o'clock we went to the byres where be milk it and the old lady milked the cattle and she sieved it out and was very particular about it and would give us a drink of the hot milk and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was that in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes, oh yes, just out there. Where the car park - there at the foot of the Burgh Road. You see, at that time - you know the Burgh Road? Well that was - boundary between Lerwick and the - and the country. That was the boundary at Lerwick. At the 
east side where the houses live paid the rates to the Town Council. At the other side of the road paid them to the Country. Just - just down here was the boundary of Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So they had a farm inside the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes, yes. Oh they had it all there, yes, I do - well it was just outside the burgh where they had the farm. Yes, and they }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 kept}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  maybe about - at that time maybe twelve or fourteen milking cattle. And this old lady milked them and we delivered that. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 And that people had a carting establishment, kept maybe about - oh eighty cart horses and maybe couple that they used for driving and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4485709\charrsid8147471 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  - that man I think paid fifteen shillings a week and he had to be up at six o'clock in the morning, before six. And that man had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4485709\charrsid8147471 contract}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  for the
 coal, distributing the coal, it was all coal in Lerwick. And he had to get up and - brush down the horse and give him a feed and then he went for his breakfast he would working and carting 'til nine and he - went for his breakfast, started again at ten a
nd so on, 'til six o'clock at night. And then he had to come back at night and - brush down the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 and give the horse a supper, so he was working a good long day. And then he had to look after the horse all day on Sunday. Get up and give the horse his br
eakfast and his dinner and bush him down and - and he had fifteen shillings a week. And a married man maybe. Yes. Of course in the old days you know, men that were working outside it would come bad weather, couldn't work, they got nothing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there a lot of poverty in the town at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh yes, the people werena very well off. You see, the men were all working on an outside job in building and that. Well you couldn't build with bad weather and he didna get any pay. And there was - I wouldna
 say that they were just - what you'd term very bad poverty but - but they werena very well off, put it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 If you were a craftsman like you - were you were better off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes. Oh you were better - oh you were better off 'cos you was alway
s working, yes, inside, oh yes. Yes. But a great a lot of it at then - at these days it was piecework. Like all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 tailors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 and shoemakers and coopers, they were all piecework. And the more you did the more you got. If you were a lazy kind of a worker you got nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It made you work harder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Oh you - you had - you worked.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were there trade unions in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 None here. No, no, none here at all, oh no it was much later on we had the trade unions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You say there used to strikes in the town among the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 fish workers}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Among the coopers and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 fish workers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , yes. Yes. Yes. Oh no much, they soon settled it among themselves because - well you can't let fish lie, you can maybe let some things lie and they get it fixed up as soon as possible. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Who would you say were the most important people in the town at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well do you mean we - in business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, maybe people that were Town Councillors or - or members of the Country Council or -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were there people you were specially taught to look up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh yes, well we - that's kind of natural like I think with anybody you see. You had the feeling that these people were the numbers ones. Yes. But you - you grew out of that. No, I don't think so, they
 do that yet or the people thenadays around Lerwick, one or two of them yet that thenadays they - they wouldn't have spoken to. No, but now they would bow and scrape to speak to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Like who do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Because there were more of us than there
 were of them. Some - somebody once said that the Almighty surely liked the poor the best because he made far more of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You say some of these people thought themselves superior, who do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well just business people. Maybe a solicitor a
nd - and that, just - well maybe some schoolteachers. Yes. They thought they were people apart. But when they get older you see, there are very few of their kind left. And they have very few people to speak to, so they'll speak to you know and be maybe gl
ad to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You were taught to raise your cap to people like that were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes, had to raise your cap to them. Well, you naturally did what and - and it was maybe as good that you did that, people that you considered was in the bet
ter position as yourself. Oh yes, oh my goodness - and you still do that. Done every place. Yes. I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 - thenadays you see the - all these people that lived that seemed to be in good business and that, they - they all kept maids. In their houses, bankers and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 solicitors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 and big business people, they all kept maids. Well they didna pay them very much. Maybe - ten shillings a month and they got their food and their bed. That's all finished. They can't afford to keep them now. Anybody won't work for that now.
 So they have to do the work themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you see anything of the laird in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 He came into the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes. Yes. Oh - that was - Busta. Gifford of Busta. He was one of the County property owners, the laird. A
nd before he died he'd left instructions that there were nobody attended his - to attend his funeral except his own kind. The lairds, you call them the lairds. Well - and all these people had to come along distance to funerals and there was no conveyance 
e
xcept they came on horseback. And - and I was - have been at a funeral my time where they give you refreshments. Yes. Gave you whisky, a glass of whisky, or you could take for a glass of wine. Well that - this laird as we shall call them that came to Giff
ords funeral, they got - refreshments, liquid refreshment, maybe some other. Then they had to carry the remains, the funeral, which was four or five mile to the cemetery. Well they all - were always stopping and having more refreshments and }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 one dropped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  out, two dropped out - 'til latterly there were only two and they lay down alongside the coffin. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 So they were out for the count and an old crofter come by and he saw Mr Gifford\rquote s remains in the coffin lying there and these two men. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
He went across to his house 
and got a big rug, he took the coffin up on end and put the rope round him and he took him to the grave and buried him himself. And his kind weren't to be allowed at the funeral. And he buried the laird. And - I can't mind the book - I think it was - Nais
h's or something or some of his friends wrote the story. But he wasn't bad with the people that, I mind my mother saying he owned the property and the croft they lived in but he wasna too bad with the folk that man. If you'd been - lost a cow or - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  illness or anything he'd come and given you one. Oh yes, she said that about Gifford. Yes.;
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there much charity for the poor at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - I mind an old woman that stopped up above us. Stopped there herself and I used to go on a Saturday
 to the parish council, I was a boy, and I had a red card, I have the same yet. And I got a shilling for her. One shilling. Every Saturday. 'Course a shilling could by a lot maybe. Could buy a lot. You got five fags for a penny you know. Three boxes of ma
tches for a penny and - but still, it werena much - no. But they did have other kind of things that was charitable and help with old people that was - very poorly off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were there many people in the town you thought were very poor yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, there was quite a lot. Yes. Didn't have very much. And had to be very careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were there some families you thought were rather rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh well I won't say they were too bad. No. There werena much of that here in Lerwick. No, there werena 
much of that. No. We just had one policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The policeman in the whole town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, one policeman in the whole town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 He knew everybody did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh he knew everybody.. And somebody got full of drink one night and - when the cleaner come 
into the Town Hall into the court next morning then - they would put a cow in the witness box and he was lying drunk at - only wakening up. They called him the wet hen. It was more kind of fun done about and tricks played on you around the town then. Yes,
 oh - innocent kind of fun among the boys and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Can you tell me any more stories of that sort then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I can't remember very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The wedding when they put pepper among the guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, it wasna pepper, it was some kind of - openi
ng medicine as we shall say. Kind of like the stuff they put in - they had a - put it in among the food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Another night somebody put their hand through the window and took the wedding cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes. Pinched the cake. And mind in Old Mason's H
all where people used to live at one time - the people lived upstairs and down below was the hall so they went up there to this people's hose, the old person had died, and they were going upstairs to have a dram, they had a bottle with them and when they 
scratched the; match to have a look and here was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 corpse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 lying here stretched out, hadn't got in the coffin. They slipped the bottle and fled. That was at old Mason's Hall. Yes. But, well boys would go round and maybe play tricks but - I don't think ever
 did much damage. No. You'd maybe go and lay a slate in somebody's loom where you could get up or get a cabbage, stalk of a cabbage and we used to - punch right through it you see, fill it with straw and then set a match to the straw and the straw'd just 
s
moke and get it up against somebody's keyhole and that - and blow and the smoke just filled the house and then you - fled and watched them coming out. The old men in the Garrison house. Out loud they called them. The boys - tormented them a lot. They were
 helping them for all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What about the woman with the cat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh aye, that - that woman keeping maybe thirty cats. Her name was Stove and that but she - very fond of them and she was - well she wasna bad off that woman, she was just a kind eccen
tric and she had at the back of her house like - big ribs, you see, behind rigs from here to here so that the cats couldn't get out and in. Some of the boys had a brainwave, what we thought was a brainwave. We got paint, some red paint and we painted all 
t
he bars you see, what the cat - and next morning every cat going around the red - red cats. But - oh it was only something - but the poor cat got the worst of it. The boys didna mean to be cruel you see, but they never thought of what they were doing when
 they painted - put the paint on to, the cat, poor little devil, job to get it off. You know, but there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 mind}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  who you played with as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. No. No. We were just all much the same, yes. But, oh the - not a boy left in L
erwick that I went to school with. No. There's not one girl. At all. No boys left here but myself. That I went to the school with. It's - oh some of them moved away and the others all died. But there's just one girl left here that was in the class with me
 at school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Can you tell me what weddings were like in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well - they were great then. Well you see there were no country halls then and most of the people came into Lerwick to get married and get their - their clothes made, the women, 
there were plenty of dressmakers and milliners then. And they came in here and got that and the man got his clothes. Sometimes he went in and helped the wife to buy it. And - and they married - and they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 lived}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  - every week there were weddings, country weddi
ngs here in the town. And - any amount of liquor, plenty of good fun, oh much drunk among them and plenty about. Folk dancing. And - refreshments going around all night and - right down to the conversation lozenges as we called them you see, the square sw
eeties with the writing on it, I love you and you love me and - pass them around and - all good fun. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did the church not mind dancing, did the church disapprove of dancing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - the only church that did that was the Wesleyans. We had the We
sleyans here in Shetland you know. There are no Wesleyans in the Orkney. But the - the members of the Wesleyan church were not supposed to dance }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , but I never heard any thing about other people - maybe the Baptists or the practiced group but not - not the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Not the church of Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, the minister danced as well and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 
Oh yes, I mind the minister - oh yes indeed, there do so yet and they went to the guising at Uphelly-a. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, the ministers and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 
sheriff}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  and all them took part in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have a wedding like that yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
No, it was unfortunate that I had - didn't marry here. I went to Aberdeen owing to certain circumstances. Yes. My wife's parents, so we sent and married in the church in Aberdeen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was that before 1913?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I married 1911. Yes, 1911. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And you came back and lived here though, you didn't move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, I just lived - came back and - and stopped here ever since. And - that was all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When you were married did you help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh no, you see I was working from seven o'clock in the morning maybe nine o'clock at night and I never - was able to do very much. No. My wife -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She did it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did it all. Yes. Yes. She stopped home. At that time very few married women ever went to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She stopped working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, oh she stopped working when we married, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Had she been working before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, she was working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What was she doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She was in charge of a dairy. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Up here or in Aberdeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, no. No, here in Lerwick. No, she belonged to Lerwick the same as me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did she do even the decorating on the house or would you have somebody in to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh we had somebody in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You didn't light the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Me? Oh no, no. I never lit the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You were always working then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, yes, yes. We had gas fires and I made the tea morning, went up and give it her to waken herself up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You were up first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, I always rose first 
and went down and - got dressed and made the tea, everything was all ready and - made the tea and given her a cup of tea and - away I went. Then I come back for the nine o'clock for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 
oatmeal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  poultice. Maybe -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You worked quite a long time before breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes - oh yes. We used to go at seven and sometimes earlier. And we always came }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 home}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  for our breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you say there was much difference between the food when you were a boy and just before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I don't think it - just much the - no, no, food hasn't changed so much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you eating any more tinned food by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 There were no tinned foods then. No, as I told you just about the corned beef. And there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 were nothing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  packaged you see, nay tea,
 nor sugar nor flour or oatmeal. Nothing you bought was packaged. - Everything is packaged now. You went into a shop and you had your penny and you bought a pennyworth of sweets, well he took a piece of newspaper and he made what we call a pack you know, 
he put them in there. He didna go to no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 pens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 with paper - paper bags. He bought a bar of chocolate there was no paper. Everything is packaged now - which is much better. But a grocer had to do a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 great lot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  of things then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have to measure a man's foot when you made a shoe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh yes, oh we measured them, the width and the length and - if he had any bunions or any corns and - we - put all that - so when he put his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 foot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  in there was room for that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you keep the customer's last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes. Had his name on them. Had his name of them, yes. All - all that had anything wrong with his feet. Just the people generally we just - had maybe five or six hundred pair or lasts and - wood - wooden lasts, all wood. But like people that had - disf
igurement on their feet and that we kept their lasts just for themselves and built up to suit to so they put them on and he didna feel anything pinching him. In fact, a man with very bad feet, we hade them go so far with what we called dressing attendant,
 took the last out and he tried it on and if it was pinching here or there then we altered. That was special occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you living at home until you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, I was living at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And then you moved to a house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, yes, house of my own. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 That was - St Olaf Street. Yes. Yes. That's where -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, two rooms. Large rooms. Two very large rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was that a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And a - a living room. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 There was a kitchen as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes. We slept in the kitchen. Yes, a big room, yes, much big as this. Big room and we slept in the kitchen. Most of the people did that time of day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did you cook on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Coal. Coal range. And we had a gas ring. But - we were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 had}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  got to the stage of the gas stoves and the gas - cookers then, there were no gas cookers. No. But we - when we come home then we had gas cookers and - and then we changed over for electricity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How long did you stay in that house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Just about - thirteen year I think. Yes. It was a new house. New.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And you moved into this house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes. That was a new house that we went in. I was the first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 tenant}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  in there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You had to move out because you had a family then?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes. But - this is council houses and all built of stone and - oh yes, oh yes, all built and very nice houses. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Some of the first council houses were some of the best weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. 'Til they started to build them of - this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 concrete}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  blocks and that but - and we - there's some here built of brick but this is all stone/house. Yes, all quarried here and dressed here and everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When you were first married would you and your wife go out to see friends in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, sometimes and have friends in and - and she - was - very musical, played the piano and - and was a singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So you had musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, we had friends in and had music and the singing and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 People really made their own entertainments then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh all that, all your own entertainment then you see. Yes, yes. I remember when the old little thing of a gramophone came. And - the records was little - round like say a - like
 a tumbler and you slid them onto the roller here. The thing wasn't much bigger than this, that-s first ones that ever was, Gem. Yes. And I mind a man coming up here and he had one of these - phonographs as they were called then and he had a glass case an
d a our table and he gave you a pair of earphones and you put them in, you paid a penny and you listened to the tune.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - let me see - 19 - maybe about 1916 - '15 or '16, that would be. Maybe before then. Yes. Yes. But that's - they'd no }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 auxiliaries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 of no kind. No. Wholesale, yes. And all - well, the crofters had no ploughs, they just dug them with spades. Dug the land maybe six of them in a row going and turning in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you say that with your own children you tried to bring them up as you'd been brought up or did you have different ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, I just tried to bring them up the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The same attitude to punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, that's right, I just had the two - two girls and -
 and they were both very musical. I say very. And my wife was very musical. She'd - and a beautiful alto singer. So maybe they had the advantage of us. And they - they were both very musical and we had many happy times when they were young. With music and
 
that. And I remember they were always wanting me to buy them a gramophone and I said they would learn to play the music themself and then the - when - the wireless came, it was a while before I bought one. I wanted them, I told them they would learn to pl
ay and provide their own music and we would buy one. And they did learn and they were both very good at it. And Vera did learn the violin as well. Yes. But oh - it's all changed. And for the better.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When do you think it started changing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well I think after the first world war. Yes. First world war and that time - you see, during the war everybody has money. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 All in reparation loans and plenty of work and - and folk wouldna come back to that conditions. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And I think it helped improve that part of - 
it, a lot. And - and then we got trade unions throughout the country and people - not just like all over Britain and now everywhere had been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 browbeaten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  by this so called lairds. And you would agree with that, even I don't know what class you come from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So you think the change is for the better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Oh - oh - oh - oh much better, yes, much better, oh aye. 'Course you live, I mean just take it up here. Oh the people - well you can go around Shetland, you never see any poor people in Shetland. Absolutel
y none. No. I remind - just about the end of the war there was a fisherman paying surtax. And he hopped off rather than pay the surtax.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you feel strongly yourself about poverty in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh as I grew older. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When did you start to feel like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 That it was better? During the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, when did you start to .....? 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I think may be when I was about - fifteen or that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you try to do anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did you do yourself then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh 
well I - didna do very much, and you were powerless to do very much but when I got up to be twenty-one and - I know I remember I took an interest in the politics and even got a lodger's vote then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have to apply for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, you - you asked for it, or - well there was several of us that got together and we got a solicitor, I think you had to go before the 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 sheriff}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  with it. And - we got lodger's vote. Got interested in the politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever canvass people at elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes. Yes, yes. For Labour, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And the Liberals before that or when did you start supporting Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh all the time. All the time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 From when you were twenty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You must be one of the first Labour supporters up here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes. Yes. We had at that time what was called the Social Democratic Federation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you a member of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes. Yes. And they had meetings here in Lerwick and - put up - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 
candidates}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 , Labour candidates. Yes. And they got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. And we had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 On the council you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, on the council, yes, just on the council. Yes. Town council. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Can you tell me about when you first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 heard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  about that, did you go to a meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well 
I think the first that I maybe got interested in it was there were youth - there were men that come up during the summer time. I understand that they were on their holidays and this very high M.P. and that kind of people and they used to have outside meet
i
ngs every night, you see, there were no cars and you could stand any-where in Commercial Street or on the Esplanade and have a meeting. And they had these meetings every night and - and people stood and listened, they'd nothing else to do, there were noth
ing to bother them. No cars, you didna - and that was the first that attracted me to that sort of thing. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever speak yourself at meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well a little. Oh yes. But I - never stood for anything. No, I never did that. But this - that
 was the first man that raised that feelings in me and all - plenty of other people in Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Can you tell me the kind of - you probably read a lot of political pamphlets at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Which were the writers you liked best yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you remember Robert Blatchford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh aye, yes, oh yes, that - that - that part of it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you take a political paper, the Clarion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, no. No. I never took that papers, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever read any Marx?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I've read some of it, yes. But being a very strong churchman that was only my objections.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You objected to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I objected to their opinions about the church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The people in the Social Democrats were hostile to the church here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Some of them were, yes. Some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But others weren't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
I've been convinced all me life of the - Labour paper and also the I.L.P. and all that but then I'm more - a lesser - sort of position against the church but we've been governed by Labour for many many years past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But the I.L.P. wasn't so against the church as the S.D.S.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But there wasn't a branch of the I.L.P.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was there a branch here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Just the S.D.S.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Y
es. Yes. But I - I thought that, I don't know, I might be very far wrong 'cos nobody bothering very much with churches nowadays in any case. Yes. Oh a certain amount of people up there that comes to church and - we had and income about five thousand twent
y years by the people at the Manse, yes. The last communion Sunday we had here on the Sunday morning we had two hundred pound in the collection so you - you see there are still some people interested in the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 If somebody in the community does something that people disapprove of, the elders go and talk to them about it don't they?}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well they used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They don't do that any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. They don't do that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did they when you were younger though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, they did, oh aye, yes, they did when I was younger and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You and your brothers were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 elders}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  of the church, are they still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 they\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  both dead now. One lived 'til he was seventy and the other was seventy-six. He died in - Bertie died in 1964.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They were in business in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes- Yes. Like in the May, the - the herring fishing with the nets, the drift net, the - every place around Shetland all had curing stations and you could say there would have been about a thousand sailboats. At that time. 
And gradually when the steam drifter started to come the sailboats - drifted away and it was all steam drifters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When was the change?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh I would say the change would have been - let me see 1900 and I was fourteen, maybe about 1906 - no, 1900 - 
1902 or 1903, it began gradually and then it all steam. And then the boats - after the steam it became motor. The steam drifters all drifted away and then we got all the sailboats fitted with - motor engines. And then we got the boat bigger and weigh - se
v
enty - some of them eighty feet and previous to that when I mind them first they were boats just about forty feet and used sails. But then you maybe had here at one time about five hundred steam drifters and every one of that was shooting a hundred nets e
ach. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 You can - miles, miles of nets, each boat.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did they all come in at once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, oh at the weekend. And then we had all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6564853\charrsid8147471 Dutchmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 . That time, from 1900 or 1910 or that, there been in the Lerwick harbour about anywhere up to three hundred, ma
ybe sometimes more, Dutch fishing vessels. Mostly sail. And - our own Lerwick, well you couldn't move for the Dutchmen - they all wore just wooden clogs and all the great baggy trousers and all that on. And - they - they were great on buying sweets, I rem
e
mber one shop telling me he took in a quarter of a ton - of peppermints, you know what the peppermints, round, and the pear drops, that's all the kind, and he had them all in pound tins and he sold to the Dutchmen. For about maybe threepence ha'penny or f
o
urpence a pound. And you'd seen 'em going over the street with a big net and maybe about a dozen of this tins of pear drops and - great on that because it was taxed but you could buy a ground of tobacco from a Dutchman for - for a shilling. And a hundred 
c
igars for a bob. A Dutchman you see, there were no tax on the tobacco there. And - they all cured their own fish aboard their own ship. Yes. The Dutchmen, yes. And when they got their cargo then they went home with it. Yes, they used to say you know at Am
sterdam was built out of the back of Bressay. Where they fish. But you usually had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 during}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 the season about three hundred in the harbour. Couldn't move - ships couldn't move for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And the streets were crowded then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 crowded}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 . Crowded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 All the shops were busier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, they bought a great lot of these sweets. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
And knives. Well I think it was to use }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 aboard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 ships and that and for gutting the fish. Yes. And - but they were wine - and there were no trouble with them. Oh you couldna move in Commercial Street for them on a weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 And you'd have all the herring girls in?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, well that was - that was the local curer. Oh my goodness me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I thought there were girls who came from the mainland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh came - oh they came in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 shiploads}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  of them. Went to Stornaway and came around Cape Wrath maybe with two or three hundred of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Where did they sleep when they were here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh they had all huts out there what they call Grimista and they all had their own piers and st
ations all built and they had all the huts ready for the girls to live in this huts. Wooden beds and that and - two tier. Yes, yes. They come up here for the fishing and the fishing last maybe for three month anyway and maybe sometimes longer. Yes. Then t
hey used to fish the herring later, like this time of year they fish the herring which we call spent, after the herring had spawned. And - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 Russians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  at that time bought them all. They could eat anything. Russians - way back in 1900. But - the Dutchman }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
 took and went over as soon as he got this - all his barrels and his holds full up then he went back to his own country, sold them there. But all the rest - I think the largest curer ever in was in one year maybe would have been about - oh 1907 or 1908, w
as one million barrels that was cured in Shetland. That was a lot of herring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What about whale fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well we had the whale fishing not - not here in Lerwick, up in - where you passed there at - Voe. And there were two stations there and they w
ere one, two and - Ronas Voe and two at Colla Firth, North Mainland. And we - they were Norwegians, northern - northern - well Norwegians but they employed all local people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 
And then they, these little ships would go - went out and harpooned the whales. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Ma
ybe went out and he harpooned one and he - and then he - put a hole on him and tightened him up and everything and anything and pump them full air. Took it up to - left him by and then he went and maybe fished another one. Then there would be two. Oh you 
could feel the smell of them here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I wonder why they were Norwegians that ran those ships?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well I don't know, they were the people that was great whalers you know and then they used to go to the South Shetlands, Salvesen and Shap Ness and Leith.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you describe the House, it was a flat wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, it was a three flatted house, we lived in the second flat. Two rooms. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 One was the bedroom and the other was a sort of living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - one was a - just a living room and the other was a sitting room. Kitchen separate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You mean there was a bedroom as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, there was no bedroom. Well we had a - bed in the - in the kitchen, like the living room, and a bed in the sitting room. Recesses. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So you had your meals in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And was there a kind of range there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, a range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Coal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 There was no gas laid on there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, there was no gas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Your father's house in the town had gas I seem to remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, but not for cooking. Just gas for light. Yes, gas light.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you tell me about the kind of cooking that your mother did then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Just plain good cooking she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you describe a sort of typical day's meals, what would you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well we would have porridge every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And - we used to vary it at times. Perhaps eggs, boiled eggs and - porridge, tea and toast.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What about midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well we got perhaps soup or - a steak pie sh
e used to make every Sunday. And - plum pudding she used to make a lot of and - got fish and - mince and - just the usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you have something else in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we just had our tea about - six or - between five and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What did that consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 We got tea and plain bread and - perhaps eggs or - something fried. Perhaps dumplings, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did she do her own baking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, she baked, yes. Oat cakes and bannocks and - all this, yes, pan cakes. She did a lot of baking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, her own jam, rhubarb jam and plum jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Any bottling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, she bottled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What would she bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Don't know. But we did get bottled fruit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. Didn't get much pickle, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 She wouldn't do any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. There was no wine in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 How often would you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Perhaps three times or four times a week, we got a lot of meat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And on Sunday you had steak pie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 We always got the steak pie. With the pastry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever have rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 It wasn't possible to keep any hens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, not in the - flat. No, we didn't have hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you tell me about how the meals were served, you would all sit at the table together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, always the table was set. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And grace was said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Always grace said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have to wait to the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, we always had to wait. No one was allowed to leave the table. Just a big table in the living room. We all sat down together.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And your mother would serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 did she allow you to sort of pick and choose from the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, not much, no, just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You had to have what was given to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would she be upset if you left things uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, we had to clean up the plate.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And you were allowed to ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was she strict about sitting and holding and knives and forks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we were trained to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You would say she was fairly strict about it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, she was fairly strict, what to do, how to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What about bringing something like a book or a toy to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you tell me something about the housework, would you use a laundry or do the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well she had a wash house, there's a washhouse down - the foot of steps where we stayed, and - all the tenants had a special day that they went down and did their washing which - seemed to be a bad day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So they had turns in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
They had turns in this wash house. Yes. It had two deep sinks you know and a great big boiler that you put coal - with a fire underneath it that she boiled all the clothes. And there's always a very strong smell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
And they starched everything you know, the tablecloths, pillowcases and - curtains that went across the beds you know. She used to starch them all, they were all white. And the curtains that went around the foot of the bed. Everything was all starched.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you expected to help in that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well I don't remember us helping much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you remember being expected to help with the housework, doing any little things in the house or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well - not much, I was very young then, at that house, but I don't remember that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Later on you did things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes. But it was always a big day when we went down to the - wash house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would your mother make clothes for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, she knitted a lot of our clothes, dresses and underwear and - and socks - stockings
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And you would also buy new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 In Lerwick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What sort of shops did they have here for clothes at that time, were they sort of tailors shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Like a tailors shop. We got a dressmaker - to make our dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They weren't ready made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
No, no, they weren't ready made. Just went and got fitted for it. There used to be a lot of serge, navy serge. And tweed. But she made all our - dresses mostly. Skirts and jumpers and - stockings and underwear she made at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And your father made the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 That's right. Made shoes and boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You said his hours of work were so long that he couldn't help at all in the house, do you 
remember him doing anything to help in the house like making a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes. I remember him doing - if my mother was going to a gathering or anything }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 he would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  - look after us and give us supper and put us to bed. Yes. Yes. Yes. He was very good like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What about doing any cleaning in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I don't remember him cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
You would get somebody in to do the repairs and things like that rather than do it yourselves, or would he sort of set to at the weekends and do a bit of painting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, we always got a decorator in, we never did - decorating, my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you expected to go to bed at a fixed time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we had to go at a fixed time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Was that fairly late, round about ten?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh no, much earlier we went to bed, oh yes. About nine o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Could you tell me about discipline in the family, would your father and mother simply sort of reprimand you if they disapproved of something you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They didn't use physical punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. No. No, I don't remember any - a smack now and then, yes, but not on any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But the main way would be to talk to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Oh yes, to talk to us. Yes. We were very strictly - brought up. And I think it was fairly good because it -
 stays with you the rest of your life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you remember the sort of things then they would emphasise as being important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well good behaviour and not to talk back to them and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we went to church every Sunday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 If grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I don't think so, no. We'd be - trying to listen, but we didn't - we weren't allowed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we were, yes. We were allowed to talk during meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Could you tell me about birthdays, were there any special things that happened on a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes, we'd always have a - something extra, perhaps it wasn't much you know. Yes. Little presents, not anything. There wasn't very much - money then o
f course. But we used to get - what we got we appreciated, when I look back it wasn't much to what they get nowadays. Maybe a hanky or a soft ball or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you have a party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we got a little. After our tea perhaps
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever go on outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, we went for picnics. Yes. We walked of course. Out to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 beaches}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 . The hillock, this hillock here. And - and we'd sit and have our picnic and mother made, and take a flask of tea, and we'd go to the peat hill. Because we had peats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You cut your own peats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes. We cut peats. So we'd make it a day and go there and that was a - a little treat when we went for the peats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Everybody in the town had the right to cut peats, is that the way it is, or do you have to rent a piece?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Used to rent a piece, yes, yes, you pay so much, ten shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You mean your father and mother would go up there and your father would cut it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, and brought the peats in. Yes. We went. Perhaps a school
 in the morning but it was a holiday in town, we'd always - go to the peat hill, that would be our outing. Special day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 A Bank Holiday you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What would happen on a Saturday, would that be the sort of thing you'd do on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
No, not on a Saturday. Wednesday would be the holiday, yes, never a Saturday. Saturday would be a shopping day, special day, late - shops closed then late Saturday nights. Perhaps about ten o'clock. It would never be a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You would go shopping with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you have an impression if there was a lot of sort of visiting in the house, people calling in and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. There was a lot of visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The open door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The open door, it was always the open door. Friends coming in to pass the evening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Perhaps musical evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Your father was telling me about this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You were all musical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You told me quite a lot about Sundays at that time but did they think it wrong for you to play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Yes, we weren't allowed out. No, we weren't allowed to play. Just went for walks and - home again. Just walking. Yes, but not to play. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, played snakes and ladders. Ludo and snakes and ladders. Snap, we played snap games and happy families we played.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Just to the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Where would you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 We stayed with friends of my mother's, down in Conisborough, and Levenwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What could you do when you went down there just walk around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well it was a farm we went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did you help on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, help on the farm, for hay. And with the hens and - the peats they collected in the little carts, fetched the peats from the hill.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did the country seem to be very different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Very different, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Can you tell me what sort of things struck you about it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well the - perhaps the beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The box beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The box beds they had, and it seemed to be straw - that we slept on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were those the beds that you actually had doors that shut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, they had doors that shut. It seemed very hot - in those beds. The food was very different. Well they just used to boil a gr
eat pot of potatoes, and the potatoes were just put in the middle of the table and - just helped yourself out of a great big pot, yes, and great big plates of semolina, rice. Big plates you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Were their table manners much less formal, less strict, they would help themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, you'd help yourself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They were much more easy going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Easy going, yes. Yes. We all seemed to have a big meal at night before we went to bed. Perhaps bit porridge or - and semolina again maybe, semolina pudding. We got that before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you remember any story telling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And playing the fiddle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Yes. Of course it was in the summertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So there wasn't so much of it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Not so much then. But all the people gathered at the houses. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 And that was something that you hadn't found here, the music was very different in the town was it, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, it was different. There was no piano there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Did people not play the fiddle so much in the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well my father played the fiddle so I was brought up with the violin, I'm a violinist myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 So it was more the piano not being there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They used to have organs, a lot of organs in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you mean a sort of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 melodeon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, just organ. Just a little organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 I don't know whether I know what you mean. It's something you hold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. This stands on the floor. Yes. Harmoniums they called them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Miniature ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, miniature ones. A cover used to fol
d down over the keyboard, press the top down. Like these little organs in some of the houses, and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
, with a great big horn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 You had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471  here though didn't you? I remember your father mentioning getting a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. Bu
t they had them in the country though. Some of them, not all of them, because they weren't very - well off, the people. Just crafting people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 When you went down there would your father join in the story telling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, he did. He used to come down every Saturday night. Yes. He never got the holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But he went out to the country every Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 He came down every Saturday when we were there and went home of the Sunday. Yes. He never seemed to take a holiday, likely he couldn't af
ford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 But you do remember him joining in the story telling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, I remember him joining in. He came down - he always had fruit with him of a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 They would get that off the boats you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, he would come down from Lerwick he used to get the - the fruit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you think most people in the town would have country relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
Well not all But we went down to this - croft, we enjoyed it, we used to go down - play in the burns you know and pick up perhaps and any little
 stones and Make a lot of boats out of the iris leave you know. Sail them down the - this little burn. Went to the sheep dippings. Shearing the sheep and all that we went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you remember your mother having outside interests, interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4485709\charrsid8147471 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
? she did. She used to - help at concerts with the children, she'd have concerts with the church - for the children. Of course she knitted a lot so she wasn't much out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Spent most of the evenings knitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would she ever go out just to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No. Perhaps to the church Guild but that's all. But never - out to enjoy herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Would you say at that time that on the whole your mother and father would share their friends or would your mother have a 
set of women friends and your father a set of men friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 No, they shared their friends, my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you think that was typical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, I think it was. Always shared their friends. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you think people were very tolerant of each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Very tolerant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 That's one of the risks with knowing everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, but they seemed to be very tolerant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Do you remember any savings clubs like sick clubs, boot clubs, do you know what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 What do you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Well they have these things where you pay in a penny a week and then if you're ill you get benefit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15354761\charrsid8147471 Aconites}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 . The - he told me about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 He mentioned the ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6381548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 Yes, he paid in every week to the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4485709\charrsid8147471 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 . Yes. And the Oddfellows, I think that was the - didn't he tell you about the Oddfellows? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16262158 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 The}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8147471  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13324050\charrsid8147471 
were a kind of temperance order weren't they?
